Gradient descent in practice 1 : Feature Scaling

We can speed up gradient descent by having each of our input values in roughly the same range.
This is because will descend quickly on small ranges and slowly on large ranges, and so will oscillate inefficiently down to the optimum when the variables are very uneven.

The way to prevent this is to modify the ranges of our input variables so that they are all roughly the same.

[-1, +1] [-0.5, +0.5]

These arent exact requirements; we are only trying to speed things up.
The goal is to get all input variables into roughly one of these ranges
